==Indonesian==

===Pronunciation===
{{rfap}}

===Adjective===
'''cuek'''
popularized by Ruth Sahanaya in her 80s hit Astaga!; probably derived from the Malay word [[cuai]], that means negligent. 
#to be easy going. ''Dia orangnya '''cuek''' '' means ''He is an '''easy going''' person''

===Verb===
'''cuek'''

popularized by Ruth Sahanaya in her 80s hit Astaga!; probably derived from the Malay word [[cuai]], that means negligent.

====Definition====
#to ignore. See below for example.
#to take something easy. ''Dia '''cuek''' aja, padahal ceweknya selingkuh'' / '' He's '''taking it easy''' although his girlfriend is having an affair''

====Transformation====
* '''nyuekin''': Active Transitive Verb with affix '''me-V-i'''. ''Kamu kok '''nyuekin''' gue?'' means ''Why do you '''ignore''' me?''
* '''dicuekin''': Passive Verb with affix '''di-V-i'''. ''Gue '''dicuekin''' dia !''' means ''I '''am ignored''' by him!''

